# Environment Variables for Vercel Deployment

## Frontend Environment Variables (Add to Vercel Project Settings)

```
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-vercel-app.vercel.app/api
```

## Backend Environment Variables (Add to Vercel Project Settings)

```
# Database
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/servisbeta?retryWrites=true&w=majority
DB_NAME=servisbeta

# JWT Authentication
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_here
JWT_EXPIRE=30d

# Environment
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000

# CORS Settings
CLIENT_URL=https://your-vercel-app.vercel.app
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-vercel-app.vercel.app

# Cloudinary Configuration
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloudinary_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_cloudinary_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_cloudinary_api_secret

# Email Configuration
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USER=horlartundhey@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=your_gmail_app_password
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@servisbeta.com

# Security
BCRYPT_SALT_ROUNDS=12
```

## How to Set Up Environment Variables in Vercel

1. Go to your Vercel project dashboard
2. Navigate to "Settings" â†’ "Environment Variables"
3. Add each variable one by one:
   - **Name**: Variable name (e.g., `MONGO_URI`)
   - **Value**: Variable value (your actual credentials)
   - **Environment**: Select "Production", "Preview", and "Development" as needed

## Important Notes for Production

1. **Replace placeholder values** with your actual credentials
2. **Update `VITE_API_BASE_URL`** with your actual Vercel app URL
3. **Update `CLIENT_URL` and `ALLOWED_ORIGINS`** with your actual Vercel app URL
4. **Use production MongoDB cluster** (not development/test database)
5. **Generate a new JWT_SECRET** for production
6. **Use Gmail App Password** for EMAIL_PASS (not regular password)

## Quick Setup Commands

After setting up environment variables in Vercel:

```bash
# Install Vercel CLI (if not already installed)
npm install -g vercel

# Login to Vercel
vercel login

# Deploy from project root
vercel

# Or for production deployment
vercel --prod
```
